      <title>FBI says deadly New Orleans attack suspect acted alone. And, the House speaker vote</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/01/03/g-s1-40945/up-first-newsletter-new-orleans-deadly-attack-mike-johnson-house-speaker-vote</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/01/03/g-s1-40945/up-first-newsletter-new-orleans-deadly-attack-mike-johnson-house-speaker-vote</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/01/03/g-s1-40945/up-first-newsletter-new-orleans-deadly-attack-mike-johnson-house-speaker-vote</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 13:07:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The FBI says Shamsud-Din Jabbar, the driver who rammed a pickup truck into a crowd in New Orleans on New Year's Day, acted alone. &lt;/strong&gt;The &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/02/nx-s1-5245814/new-orleans-truck-attack-latest-fbi" target="_blank"&gt;agency backed off of an earlier statement&lt;/a&gt; that Jabbar was "not solely responsible" for the attack that left at least 14 people dead.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40855" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2324;         --source-height: 1307;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2324x1307+0+303/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F5e%2F873654b8429b89807ceef7c84475%2Fap25002628222069.jpg" class="img" alt="A state trooper stands by New Orleans&amp;#039; Canal and Bourbon streets on Thursday, the day after a truck slammed into a crowd on Bourbon Street, killing at least 14 people." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A state trooper stands by New Orleans' Canal and Bourbon streets on Thursday, the day after a truck slammed into a crowd on Bourbon Street, killing at least 14 people.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          George Walker IV/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;A better look at surveillance footage revealed Jabbar placing explosive devices concealed in coolers in the French Quarter&lt;/strong&gt;, an act the FBI previously thought he had help with, NPR's Debbie Elliot tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. The FBI also found that Jabbar posted several &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1222640170:1264256779" target="_blank"&gt;online videos proclaiming support for ISIS&lt;/a&gt;. New Orleans is determined not to let the attack sap the city's culture. Drummer Darnell Simms tells Elliot that he wants to let people know "the love is still out here." This event has shaken people up, and soon, national events like the Super Bowl and Mardi Gras will draw millions to the city.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Bourbon Street re-opened yesterday afternoon, over 24 hours after the attack.&lt;/strong&gt; The scene was cleared just in time for the Sugar Bowl, a NCAA College Football Playoff game. Check out photos of Bourbon Street's reopening &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/01/02/g-s1-40913/photos-bourbon-street-reopens-new-orleans-truck-attack" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Pedicab driver Tyler Burt ended a long day of work on New Year's Eve&lt;/strong&gt; with a short ride that took him to the start of Bourbon Street. He gives NPR network station WWNO &lt;a href="https://www.wwno.org/wwno/2025-01-02/eyewitness-to-tragedy-a-pedicab-drivers-view-of-the-bourbon-street-attack" target="_blank"&gt;an eyewitness account&lt;/a&gt; of the tragedy.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Kareem Badawi had just finished his first semester at the University of Alabama&lt;/strong&gt;, where he was studying engineering. His father &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5246110:nx-s1-5311337-1" target="_blank"&gt;speaks to &lt;em&gt;All Things Considered &lt;/em&gt;about losing Badawi&lt;/a&gt; in the attack.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A new Congress is set to be sworn in today. The first order of business in the House is to elect a speaker.&lt;/strong&gt; Republicans have a narrow majority, meaning they must almost unanimously decide on a leader. House Speaker Mike Johnson has the endorsement of President-elect Donald Trump, but he faces the challenge of some GOP holdouts. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Trump's endorsement is key to the position but may not be enough for Johnson&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Claudia Grisales says. Johnson &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1222640170:1264256779" target="_blank"&gt;faces tight margins and will need a simple majority&lt;/a&gt; of the 435-member House. He needs 218 votes, and there are 219 Republicans, leaving him little breathing room. Democrats are not expected to help Johnson or any other Republican get over the line. GOP congressman Thomas Massie of Kentucky has been vocal about voting against Johnson. "That could open the floodgates for other House Republicans who'd like to vote no on Johnson," Grisales says.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The FBI is sharing new details and footage about the person who planted pipe bombs in Washington, D.C.&lt;/strong&gt;, on the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/02/nx-s1-5244008/fbi-pipe-bomb-jan6-dnc-rnc" target="_blank"&gt;night before the Jan. 6 riot at the U.S. Capitol&lt;/a&gt; in 2021. The agency is still trying to identify the person who placed the devices, which didn't detonate. Authorities have combed through 39,000 videos, conducted 1,000 interviews and sifted through 600 tips, but the alleged bomber remains elusive. For the first time, the FBI shared an estimated height of the person — approximately 5 feet 7 inches tall — as one of the details they hope will lead to the suspect's capture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;25 goals for 2025&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40946" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1097;         --source-height: 617;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1097x617+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7c%2Fff%2F709e6d144f83b92befc2925da815%2Flife-kit-budget-small-custom-978a0e330eec2985a7136e351d50906299ca13e3.jpg" class="img" alt="." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 .                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Shannon Wright for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Can't decide on a resolution for 2025? NPR's Life Kit has expert guides to make any goal a reality. We'll share a few of them every week this month. View all 25 guides &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/01/g-s1-38433/new-years-resolution" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;here&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keeping tabs on where your money is going is a good first step to cutting back on spending&lt;/strong&gt; and saving more. Here are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/01/09/683530953/be-the-master-of-your-budget" target="_blank"&gt;some budgeting tips&lt;/a&gt; to get you started and make more informed decisions about your money: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 &lt;strong&gt;Don't budget just because you think you should&lt;/strong&gt;; instead, set a specific goal that has meaning to you.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 &lt;strong&gt;Take advantage of the budgeting momentum that comes with big life changes — like moving or a job loss — while it lasts.&lt;/strong&gt; If you mess up or overspend later on, don't quit.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💵 &lt;strong&gt;Follow the 50-30-20 method. &lt;/strong&gt;Dedicate 50% of your take-home income to basic living expenses, 30% for discretionary expenses like entertainment and 20% for savings.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Life Kit&lt;/em&gt; has several more guides &lt;/strong&gt;to help you manage your money in 2025. Check out some of them here: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Avoid these &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/08/15/g-s1-16998/to-save-more-money-avoid-these-5-common-financial-mistakes" target="_blank"&gt;common financial mistakes&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️&lt;strong&gt; These five big purchases &lt;/strong&gt;can help you reduce your carbon footprint and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2023/10/03/1196977935/save-money-energy-tips" target="_blank"&gt;save money at home&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Have you heard of the no-buy challenge?&lt;/strong&gt; You stop spending money on non-essential items for a set period. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/09/05/g-s1-20325/could-you-live-without-shopping-for-a-year-try-the-no-buy-challenge" target="_blank"&gt;Here's how it works&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40947" class="bucketwrap image large