ality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x2000+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff2%2F38%2Fd08c50a64d8d9d7555b976cbc623%2F051324-bm-wustl-grad-21.jpeg" class="img" alt="Graduating students protests remarks by Washington University Chancellor Andrew Martin on May 13, at the university’s campus near Clayton, Mo. Full story here." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Graduating students protests remarks by Washington University Chancellor Andrew Martin on May 13, at the university's campus near Clayton, Mo. Full story &lt;a href="https://www.stlpr.org/education/2024-05-13/st-louis-washington-university-graduation-israel-palestine-war-protests"target="_blank"   &gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Brian Munoz/St. Louis Public Radio                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In 2024, photographers at NPR's member and affiliate stations captured images of &lt;/strong&gt;protests that unfolded on college campuses, a total solar eclipse, one of the most important Election Days in U.S. history, multiple celebrations and more. NPR compiled a selection of photos from this year showcasing their impactful photojournalism. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2024/12/30/g-s1-39441/2024-in-photos-npr-station-photographers" target="_blank"&gt;Click here&lt;/a&gt; to see these photos.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40468" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6106;         --source-height: 4070;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6106x4070+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F98%2F734aed9b46dcbd2f0fffb1d60d9e%2Fgettyimages-2184605718.jpg" class="img" alt="Norway&amp;#039;s chess grandmaster Magnus Carlsen gestures during a game in the Tata Steel Chess India tournament in Kolkata on Nov. 17." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Norway's chess grandmaster Magnus Carlsen gestures during a game in the Tata Steel Chess India tournament in Kolkata on Nov. 17.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Dibyangshu Sarkar/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Magnus Carlsen, the world's top chess player, is at the World Blitz Championship&lt;/strong&gt; after going head-to-head with organizers over his &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/30/g-s1-40462/magnus-carlsen-chess-jeans-dress-code-championship" target="_blank"&gt;refusal to change out of jeans&lt;/a&gt; to conform to a strict dress code at a tournament last week.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A federal appeals court has rejected an appeal by President-elect Donald Trump &lt;/strong&gt;of a 2023 jury decision &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/30/nx-s1-5243228/federal-appeal-trump-e-jean-carroll" target="_blank"&gt;that he sexually abused&lt;/a&gt; and defamed E. Jean Carroll.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The nation's biggest transit systems are using AI-enhanced cameras to keep bus lanes clear of illegally parked cars.&lt;/strong&gt; The technology, provided by start-up Hayden AI, helps transit agencies fine drivers who &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/31/nx-s1-5213674/transit-systems-ai-cameras-bus-lanes" target="_blank"&gt;block bus lanes and stops&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Obed Manuel&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
