      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Dec 2024 13:04:26 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Korea's parliament voted today to impeach acting President Han Duck-soo. &lt;/strong&gt;This comes less than a month after parliament voted to impeach President Yoon Suk Yeol for imposing martial law. The two impeachments illustrate the seriousness of the political crisis happening in one of Asia's key democracies.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40118" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5422;         --source-height: 3615;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5422x3615+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8b%2F7a%2F9da34fa24d889ab420244860e876%2Fap24361227800325.jpg" class="img" alt="South Korean acting President Han Duck-soo speaks at the government complex in Seoul, South Korea, Thursday, Dec. 26, 2024." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 South Korean acting President Han Duck-soo speaks at the government complex in Seoul, South Korea, Thursday, Dec. 26, 2024.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Choi Jae-koo/AP/Yonhap                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Han has been cited as refusing to appoint three justices to fill vacancies on the Constitutional Court, which will rule on Yoon's impeachment&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Anthony Kuhn tells&lt;em&gt; Up First&lt;/em&gt;. Han says he didn't appoint them because that's the prerogative of the president and not the acting president. The deputy prime minister and finance minister, Choi Sang-mok, is now acting president. The court has &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1221795533:1264054656" target="_blank"&gt;180 days to decide whether to remove&lt;/a&gt; or reinstate Yoon, but they say the impeachment trial is a top priority. Yoon also faces charges of insurrection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Israel launched its most aggressive attack in Yemen so far against Iran-backed Houthis yesterday. &lt;/strong&gt;The airstrikes hit the rebel-controlled capital's international airport causing damage to the runway and control tower. At least six people died and dozens were injured in the strikes, according to Yemen's state-run news agency. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; Israel says it attacked the infrastructure used as a conduit for Iranians who back Houthis rebels to smuggle weapons into the country and for entry of senior Iranian officials&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Carrie Kahn says. The head of the World Health Organization was in the airport waiting to board a flight at the time of the strike. Israel says the attack was in retaliation for missiles being fired from Yemen, which the Houthis say they &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1221795533:1264054656" target="_blank"&gt;won't stop until Israel withdraws from Gaza&lt;/a&gt;. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says the Houthis will be taken down even if it takes time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Georgia is preparing to swear in a new president, who has been a vocal critic of the West.&lt;/strong&gt; This development follows protests in the capital, Tbilisi, that erupted last month after the government decided to suspend talks to join the European Union. The country's incumbent president has refused to resign following the disputed election in October. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Mikheil Kavelashvii, a former soccer player turned politician for the Georgian Dream Party, is set to be inaugurated on Sunday. &lt;/strong&gt;He was chosen by the electoral college, a first for the country, rather than the popular vote, says Robin Forestier-Walker, a reporter following the situation in Georgia. The incumbent president, President Salome Zourabichvili, was elected by popular vote in 2018 and says the recent elections were stolen. Tensions are rising in the country as &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1221795533:1264054656" target="_blank"&gt;two potential presidents claim legitimacy&lt;/a&gt;. A significant portion of the nation is demanding new elections given that polling consistently has shown strong support for Georgia joining the EU.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-39833" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7559;         --source-height: 5039;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7559x5039+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc3%2F8b%2F859f3df94f329d851b86638c1b87%2Fgettyimages-1258676756.jpg" class="img" alt="Scammers are using generative artificial intelligence tools to create more convincing fake text and voices to commit fraud with according to a recent FBI warning to the public." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Scammers are using generative artificial intelligence tools to create more convincing fake text and voices to commit fraud with according to a recent FBI warning to the public.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Olivier Morin/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fraudsters are improving their scams with the help of artificial intelligence.&lt;/strong&gt; Generative AI has made it easier to dupe people by creating more convincing fake text messages and voices to commit scams. The FBI issued a public service announcement earlier this month, warning about AI being used to commit these crimes, especially during the holiday season. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/24/nx-s1-5235265/how-to-protect-yourself-from-holiday-ai-scams" target="_blank"&gt;Here are some tips to help&lt;/a&gt; protect yourself: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📱 &lt;strong&gt;Phishing is when bad actors try to obtain sensitive information &lt;/strong&gt;for fraudulent purposes. If you get a strange-looking message, check for misspelled words, grammatical errors, or even variations in the logos of companies claiming to be contacting you.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📱 &lt;strong&gt;Scammers just need a few seconds of your voice to create a clone&lt;/strong&gt; that they could then try to use on your friends and loved ones. Create a secret code with your loved ones to keep them safe from schemes asking for money.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📱 &lt;strong&gt;To prevent impersonation, reduce your digital footprint.&lt;/strong&gt; Set your social media accounts to private and limit the personal information you share publicly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out &lt;/strong&gt;more &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/24/nx-s1-5235265/how-to-protect-yourself-from-holiday-ai-scams" target="_blank"&gt;tips to help you avoid AI scams&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-39380" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 940;         --source-height: 529;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/940x529+105+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F8a%2Fc1%2F815d5c2c4719b6daae06dcd79b55%2Fnatures-candy.jpg" class="img" alt="Nature&amp;#039;s Candy: Timeless and Inventive Recipes for Creating and Baking with Candied Fruit" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;It's been a great year for movies. Some have included scenes and performances that have captivated audiences many months later. NPR's Aisha Harris &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/23/nx-s1-5225451/movies-2024-scenes-to-remember" target="_blank"&gt;breaks down nine such moments&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV: &lt;/strong&gt;The new series &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1198005281:1263853931" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Laid&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a dark rom-com following a woman who discovers all her exes have started to die under mysterious circumstances. This results in her taking a sexual audit of her life to warn them of their possible fate.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; Photographer Brian Kelley talked with &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition&lt;/em&gt; about &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5222562:nx-s1-5292880-1" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Parks 2&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a new book jam-packed with photos, memorabilia and essays about U.S. national parks.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;All Songs Considered &lt;/em&gt;asked listeners for songs they &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1221470987:1263880883" target="_blank"&gt;couldn't stop listening to&lt;/a&gt; this year because of how it made them feel. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/24/1221470987/songs-that-hit-hard-in-2024" target="_blank"&gt;Check out the curated playlist&lt;/a&gt; of songs that made the list.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍍 Food:&lt;/strong&gt; Camilla Wynne, a Canadian pastry chef and master food preserver, is the author of the new cookbook &lt;em&gt;Nature's Candy&lt;/em&gt;. It's an ode to the pleasures of candying fruit and baking them. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/23/nx-s1-5157794/fruitcake-natures-candy-cookbook" target="_blank"&gt;Here's one of her cake recipes to try&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-40092" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2400;         --source-height: 1601;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1601+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fed%2F05%2F6f88963944a68ae19063672c5f6d%2F20241225-bbowl-005-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1601+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brigh